    "created_at": "2014-08-04T14:30:54Z",
    "updated_at": "2014-08-04T14:30:54Z",
    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Yep, numerical testing in Excel shows that the \"V1^2 / (V1^2 - V2)\" formula approaches `(1.0 + 2.0 * com) / (2.0 * com)` as the number of samples increases -- assuming `adjust=True` and there are no missing values.\n\nI think I can implement the \"V1^2 / (V1^2 - V2)\" bias correction formula (which will depend on `adjust`, `ignore_na`, and the pattern of missing values) without resorting to writing a new `algos.ewmvar()`. So shouldn't be complicated.\n"
